review_blob: On tap @ shell cafe, not sure if it?s an old keg but very bland, almost no hop character. Kinda off forgettable.
22oz bomber, a very nice easy drinking stout. Medium body with nice roasted flavors. Great beer

Sampled from bottle at Bevmo holiday beer fest in S.F. Nice easy drinking ale, Brewery rep said it was a golden ale, not sure why R.B has it listed as a belgium ale. This beer would be great on a warm day or as a all night drinker. Have had other brews from Tap it and I continue to be impressed.
Great twist on the original racer 5. Loved this beer and cant wait to enjoy it again.
Draft: nice lacing on the glass, floral notes are amazing with citrus, has a nice grapefruit taste that you can enjoy without it being over done with hops.  A Well done Ipa
